		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> Sandwich Capital of the World (NJ) - 4/6<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(4.89)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=4170'>Pete "Ghetto 13" Flamini</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=4170&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> April 8, 2002</font><p align='justify'><blockquote><font class="bfont"> Alright, so you&#39;ve decided to read my tourney report.  Thanks.  For those of you that don&#39;t know, the Sandwich Capital of the World is a town in northern NJ called Cedar Grove.  In Cedar Grove, right next to the gaming shop, there used to be this pizza shop called Poppa Tony&#39;s that sold some of the god-awful-est pizza you&#39;ll ever taste in your life.  But somehow, Poppa Tony knew how to make the BEST chicken breast hero on the face of the earth.  Well, about a year ago, Poppa Tony had a little kitchen fire and has never re-opened because he&#39;s trying to milk his insurance company for more money.  The closing of Poppa Tony&#39;s almost directly coincided with the demise of SWCCG.  Coincidence?  I think not.<p>But now there&#39;s a deli across the street which seems to have gotten proprietary rights to all of Poppa Tony&#39;s best sandwich recipes.  Including the Chicken Breast Hero.  And to make it that much better, they sell it in a 2-foot version.  For those of you with any type of genetic disorder that prevents you from truly appreciating the magnificence of the chicken breat hero (like George), two blocks up the street is Esposito&#39;s Deli, which I think is a Mafia front (I&#39;m Italian, we can smell our own).  They make the world&#39;s greatest Roast Beef sub, thus cementing Cedar Grove&#39;s status as Sandwich Capital of the World.  If you can&#39;t find lunch in Cedar Grove, you don&#39;t deserve to eat.<p>Since I needed an excuse to drive 7 hours from Chesapeake VA to Cedar Grove NJ to get a chicken sandwich, I&#39;ve taken up LotR.  And this is my recount of my first tournament.  Obviously, I&#39;m going in with a rating of 1500, since I&#39;ve only played two games ever.  One with a starter deck where I got overwhelmed at site 5, and one with my friend Greg the night before the tournament to make sure we both understood the rules.  And that&#39;s it.  I&#39;m playing Moria Swarm for Shadow (it seemed best for helping a newbie get through his deck quickly) and Gandalf/Men with a few spells for the Fellowship.  Nothing overly original or impressive.  We end up sanctioning with 9 players, and get started a little after 4PM.  I apologize if any of the details are a little hazy, I had a long drive home to Virginia...<p>Game 1 vs. Chris Gogolen&#39;s (1671) Dwarves/Sauron<br>Chris has multiple &quot;good decks&quot;, but decided today to go with something a little more experimental.  Maybe he was doing it to give me a fighting chance, maybe he was just bored with his usual stuff.  I&#39;m pretty sure he bid three and started the Green Dragon Inn, then deployed Sam.  He got his Fellowship set up quickly with Stairs, Gimli&#39;s Axe, etc., and managed to jump over to site 3 with ease.  gosh darnit that early Gimli&#39;s Axe vs. my puny Orcs.  After complaining about how well he started, I replenish my hand and get some good stuff myself.  Glamdring, Aragorn, etc. and roll out to site 3 to keep up with him.  He got Desperate Defense of the Ring out on me right away, but I managed to get to site 3 with only 1 burden added.  The Cave Troll showed up against him at site 4, forcing him to stop for a turn.  I played Sleep during my Fellowship to get rid of DDotR, equipped a little more (I think this is where Boromir showed up), and rolled to site 4.  At site 4, a Nazgul and an Orc came down, and I moved to site 5 after using Gondor&#39;s Vengance to remove the Nazgul.  Now Thin and Stretched came down, and I added another burden for fighting with some flunkies.  At this point neither my hand nor my Shadow Conditions were overly impressive, so Chris really only had to deal with one or two weak Orcs and the Balrog at site 5.  Since the Balrog gets discarded anyway, he got to site 6 without taking too many casualties.  I started my turn by Sleeping away the T&S, deployed the Mirror (but forgot to use it), then moved into site 6 fairly healthy and giving away minimal twilight.  So I decided to skip the sanctuary and go to site 7.  This ended up being huge, because Chris got minion-screwed and had nothing to deploy giving me site 7 basically uncontested.  He healed at site 6 and moved without giving away too much twilight, but Moria did what Moria does, and used the TAC/Scimitar/Armory deal to squeeze out a low-budget Cave Troll.  This forced him to stop here just to get the Troll off the table.  I went into site 8 without too much resistance, and decided to go for site 9.  What the hell, it&#39;s my first game ever, why not be greedy.  His site 9 naturally allowed him to pull trackers, plus now he had gotten some guys in his hand, so he managed to get out (I think) 5 minions, but nobody &quot;main&quot;.  So Aragorn takes two on being the &quot;Valiant Man of the West&quot;, Gandalf and Boromir each take one on, and Frodo PATHS the remianing Vitality 1 guy.<br>Full win, 1-0, Movement: 1-3, 4-5, 6-7, 8-9.<p>Game 2 vs. Karen Prieto&#39;s (1611) Elves/Moria<br>This game was fairly slow-paced.  Both Karen and I were slower players, and we were both playing Moria designed to stop people from making double-moves.  I bid 1, she bid zero, so I went first and started the Pony.  First turn, I pulled Aragorn, gave out a sword and a staff, deployed Sam, and moved to site 3 while she set up her conditions and sent down a few minions.  I managed to use Mysterious Wizard and Servant to keep any minions from getting stacked on Swarms, for now.  Karen started Arwen and Sam, pulled Aragorn, and also made it to site 3 with minimal resistance.  I go to site 4, but those gosh darnit Goblin Patrol Troops come down along with a few other cronies, and go on the Swarms.  I put off moving to site 5 because I don&#39;t want to deal with the Troops/Balrog until I get a chance to reconcile my hand.  Karen deploys Rumil, Legolas, Aragorn&#39;s Bow, and some other basic equipment, and moves to site 4.  TAC gets me a couple minions, then the Cave Troll comes out.  But Rumil, Aragorn, and Legolas go machine-gun style and archery out everybody, and her fellowship skips into site 5.  I get out a minion and the Balrog, but one more direct archery takes out the scrub, Sam dies to the Balrog, and everybody is happy.  I move to site 5, fight the standard Swarms/Balrog Bridge type of stuff, and again, have to stop despite really only losing Sam and Thrarin.  Even with the Balrog being discarded, I didn&#39;t think I could get to the Sanctuary intact, so I had to stop again.  Karen goes into site 6 easily, but has to stop to heal all the exertions from the directed archery (this is why I say it makes no difference if you take 4 wounds from the Troll or exert 4 times to shoot it, wounds are wounds).  At the start of my turn, I finally have everything I wanted.  I Sleep away her Relics, her two Armories, her TAC, and her Swarms with two Goblin Patrol Troops on it.  I deploy the Mirror and take two minions out of her hand.  Site 6 is a cake walk, and with KIE&#39;s healing and duplicate characters I discarded, I decide I can take site 7.  I get site 7 but lose one of the guys (I can&#39;t remember if it was Aragorn or Boromir).  No big deal, I&#39;m in the lead, I&#39;ve got a shadow-heavy hand, and her Moria effects have been castrated.  I figure I can most likely win this game out.  But in the beginning of her Fellowship phase, time is called.  Decipher is so gay.  First of all, the time limit for this game needs to be extended.  But secondly, either stop right where you are at the end of time, or allow people to both have a turn.  Instead, she gives up minimal twilight and goes to site 7.  I rough her up a little and have a Cave Troll sitting around.  Normally, this would stop somebody from moving again, but since time was called, she can move again without fear of having to suffer the consequences later.  So she double moves, loses almost the entire Fellowship.  Boromir dies, Aragorn dies, Legolas dies, Arwen is exhausted.  But she gets a win because of stupid timed-game rules.  I don&#39;t blame her, she made the right play and I&#39;m sure I would have done the same thing.  But that doesn&#39;t make the rule any less gay.<br>Timed Loss, 1-1, Movement: 1-3, 4, 5, 6-7<p>Game 3 vs. Ben Still&#39;s (1575) Elves/Uruk-Hai<br>I&#39;m not quite sure who went first this game, but I believe I did since that is the only logical explanation for me getting to site 9 first moving only one site at a time.  So I bid 1, go first, pull Aragorn, his sword and the flaming brand, and a staff for Gandalf.  Sounds good, but I&#39;ll be gosh darnited if he doesn&#39;t get Lurtz down at site 2 on me because of the &quot;roaming -1&quot; on the Uruk Scout.  Gandalf takes an archery wound, then uses Mysterious to beat the scout.  Aragorn take the double-wound from Lurtz, then exerts to Gondor&#39;s Vengance him out of the way.  The three Twilight from moving to site 3 isn&#39;t enough for him to do anything, so with Lurtz gone, I go into site 3 for some much needed healing.  He starts Arwen/Legolas, and makes it to site 3 easily while I set up my effects and he archeries whatever I could manage to put down without much twilight.  I start my turn, heal, and move to site 4 without doing much of anything.  Of course, I can&#39;t find my armor so his Uruk-Hai are going to chew right through me if I double move, so I stop to clear them out.  His site 4 is underground, so the Keyward gets me the Troll for &quot;mere pennies a day&quot; and forces him to stop.  At his site 5, I make another newbie mistake by not reading all the cards on the table.  He gets down 3 Uruks, and I play Valiant Man of the West to block two of them with Aragorn for only one wound.  But I put him against the Troop of Uruk-Hai for no other reason than letting him suck up as much strength as possible, then find out the Troop cancels my strength bonus.  D&#39;oh!  Aragorn bites the big one and Gandalf gets busted again, forcing me to stop.  Then the Balrog/Ancient Chieftan make him stop.   I go into site 6 with just a busted up Gandalf and Frodo.  Frodo puts on the Ring to suck up the Assassin&#39;s archery wound, then Gandalf and Celeborn die to protect Frodo at the Sanctuary.  So now it&#39;s just Frodo, standing on the corner whistling to himself, so I stop.  The low Twilight allows him to take 6 easily, but he has to stay to heal.  I deploy Boromir with Armor, and Galadriel with Mirror, then proceed to Mirror his only two minions out of his hand.  Site 7 is mine for free, but I have to stop.  I use the TAC/Scimitar combo to draw a couple of Nazgul to stop him at site 7 as well.  At site 8, I use the mirror again to throw out Lurtz (I could only do it once because Celeborn died), and only an assassin manages to make it down on the limited twilight.  Boromir takes the archery and the skirmish wound, but I stop again.  The Cave Troll stops him at site 8 as well, plus he&#39;s not feeling too much of a rush with only Frodo and an exhausted Boromir in my party.  I discard a Boromir to heal, and move to 9.  He drops about 5 Uruks, including a Captain who pulled a guy from the discard, but since most of them were site 9 Trackers, only one guy had more than vitality 2, and none of them were Fierce.  Boromir takes an archery from another assassin, then steps in front of him and dies.  The other 4 Uruks bum-rush Frodo, only to find that &quot;the Ring had given him power according to his stature&quot; TWICE.<br>Full Win, 2-1, Movement: 1-3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8, 9<p>Game 4 vs. Greg Hodur&#39;s (1500) Gandalf-Men/Moria Swarm<br>Greg is the other guy who got into LotR strictly for the chicken sandwiches.  So neither of us ever played before, neither of us knew what was good and what wasn&#39;t, so we ended up building decks for this tournament together.  We were both playing the same Fellowship, but his shadow side was a little better than mine due to three Bill Ferny&#39;s.  I&#39;m not going to go into too much detail here, since this was just a deck playing against itself.  I bid 1 to his 0 and went first.  We both pulled Aragorn, and went straight to site 3, we both stopped at site 4 because of a Cave Troll, and we both double jumped from 5-6 after losing Sam and Thrarin to the Balrog.  We also both stopped at site 7 due to Cave Troll activity.  The biggest difference in this game was timing.  I played Sleep on his conditions early to set him back, he played Sleep on my conditions late when it really made a difference.  I got into site 8 with some minor resistance, and looked at my hand.  I had nothing shadow, and like I said, he had just removed my conditions, so TAC wasn&#39;t even an option.  If I stopped at 8, there was no way I could have prevented him from double-jumping to 9.  So I had to double jump and put it all on my Fellowship.  I managed to have just enough guys to sacrifice to his swarm.  Gandalf took on the Flankers, Boromir took on the Keyward, and Wielder of the Flame allowed Aragorn to take on the two Moria Scouts (vitality 2) with Scimitars.  All the other vitality 1 guys gang-banged on Frodo.  We resolved all the other skirmishes first (I was trying to kill enough minions to prevent Relentless), and then it came down to Frodo.  I played the PATHS and prayed he wasn&#39;t holding the Relentless, and got lucky.  That&#39;s twice this tourney that PATHS had completely saved my ass, so no matter what anybody says, two will be in every deck I make from now on.<br>Full Win, 3-1, Movement: 1-3, 4, 5-6, 7, 8-9<p>Game 5 vs. Mike Dalton&#39;s (1946) Elves & Men/Moria Swarm<br>Just in case anybody is reading this and thinking &quot;hey, the guy&#39;s not doing to bad for his first time playing&quot;, rest assured it would all blow up now.  Mike and I go back to SWCCG, so I know he&#39;s a good player.  I also knew he&#39;d be at this tourney, so I checked decktech for what he was playing nowadays, just in case.  He only had two decks listed, but both were Moria Swarm with no corruption.  So instead of bidding the 1 I had bid all day, I bid 4 in case his Fellowship bid 3 and started the Green Dragon Inn.  I won and went first, starting the Pony.  First, I forgot to draw the additional card with Gandalf, then I pulled Aragorn, did a little Fellowship equipping and moved to site 2.  We fought a few minions, but nothing so major as to stop me from getting site 3 on first turn.  Cool.  I can&#39;t remember exactly what I did, but I have the distinct feeling that I somehow stopped Mike at site 2.  Regardless, he managed to squeeze out a Cave Troll at site 4 (despite my giving him minimal twilight) forcing me to stop.  He blew right by the Sanctuary and caught up with me at site 4 as well.  Nothing of major consequence came down to greet me at site 5, so I double jumped to site 6.  I&#39;m sorry to be so sketchy with the details of this game, but the monumentous mistakes I made at site 6 were so phenomenal, I can barely remember anything else.  He took the extra Twilight, a dropped a pile of about 5 minions with weapons to greet me.  First, after his shadow pahase, I slid Aragorn over to an Orc, thus completing an assignment.  I forgot VMotW had to be played during the maneuver phase, so I lost the chance to have Aragorn suck up two Orcs.  Then, when two Orcs rushed Frodo, I played PATHS, forgetting he had TWO armories out, not one.  So the PATHS didn&#39;t work and Frodo was overwhelmed.  THEN, I realized that I had forgotten to include my Home 6 Ally in the assignment phase.  Had I fed Galadriel to the second Orc on Frodo, I also would have survived.  So basically, I made three huge, glaring, obvious, newbie mistakes, all on the same turn, that got Frodo overwhelmed.  Had I just made any two of the three dumb mistakes, Frodo would have survived and given the big pile of Shadow in my hand, I could have stopped Mike at site 5 (I think, nothing&#39;s for sure against Dalton though), healed at the Sanctuary, and moved to seven for hard-to-overcome two site lead.  Instead I stuck my head up my ass, apparently looking for more of that chicken sandwich.<br>Full Loss, 3-2, Movement: 1-3, 4, 5-6<p>So I end up 3-2 with a timed loss, which puts me snuggly in third.  Not too bad for a first time out, but still disappointing since 4-1 or even 5-0 were definitely possible.  Oh well, I learned a lot of good newbie lessons.  Play faster, remember all the phases, and above all READ THE gosh darnit CARDS.  I rare drafted Aragorn&#39;s Bow and An Able Guide for prize support, which was cool since I needed them (how do I open almost 6 boxes and never get a bow?).  Now for you people who like this kinda thing:<p>Props:<br>Mike Dalton for winning again<br>George Gundry for stealing a car and coming to hang out<br>Chris Gogolen for always being 3CG<br>Cedar Grove Deli for making a two-foot chicken breast hero<br>Cedar Grove Deli again, just because they deserve double.<p>Slops:<p>Really only me, for being such an obvious newbie/idiot at so many different points of the tourney<br>Oh, and John Lolli for once again not being around when I come up from Virginia.  He&#39;s 1 for 16 now, for a whopping .063 batting average.  Pitchershimmer better than that.  I&#39;m beginning to take this shimmer personal dawg.... <br></font></blockquote><BR><font class="bfont"> <A HREF='/lotr/treports/treports.php?id=3567&view=1&PHPSESSID=734baf00838e20bc06567a77d7e2a3a5'>Read the Reviews</a><font class="bfont"> | <A HREF='/lotr/treports/treports.php?PHPSESSID=734baf00838e20bc06567a77d7e2a3a5'>Back to List</A></font><p><font class="bfont"> <b>You must be a member to contribute to Decktech.</b>  <p>Please <a href='/lotr/main/join.php?PHPSESSID=734baf00838e20bc06567a77d7e2a3a5'> become a registered member</a></font></font></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_09.gif"></td></tr>
